#MEM id=visual-style-integrity source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/atlas/skills/custom/visual-style-integrity/SKILL.md savings=8%
M||tx|---
M||name|visual-style-integrity
M||desc|Structured "every element justifies itself" check using Dieter Rams principles. Strip tst, 3-year tst, and vt drift check. Run during style spec dv to catch decoration masquerading as direction.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|The most common fl in visual direction is adding rather than removing. A mood board w/ 12 references isn't richer — it's unfocused. A style spec w/ 6 lighting modifiers isn't precise — it's indecisive. This skill makes the removal process systematic, forcing every element to earn its presence before it reaches px.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|Test|For |
M|Test|tx|> "If I remove this element, does the im communicate something meaningfully different?"
M|Test|tx|\| Answer \| Action \|
M|Test|tx|\|--------\|--------\|
M|Test|tx|\| Yes — removing it loses something specific \| Keep it. It earns its place. \|
M|Test|tx|\| No — the im works w/o it \| Remove it. It's decoration. \|
M|Test|tx|\| Unsure \| Default to remove. Doubt = out. \|
M|Test|**El|**
M|Test|it|Each mood adjective (if 2 adjectives say the same thing, remove one)
M|Test|it|Each lighting modifier (do you need both `soft` and `diffused`?)
M|Test|it|Each colour in the palette (is each colour doing something different?)
M|Test|it|Each composition rule (do they conflict or reinforce each other?)
M|Test|it|Each item in the subject description (does every detail matter for this cg?)
M|Test|**Ta|** A style spec that passes the strip tst has no redundant elements. Every word is doing work.
M|Test|tx|---
M|Test|tx|> "wld this visual direction still feel right in 2029?"
M|Test|**Fa|**
M|Test|it|The aesthetic is rooted in a specific sl media tn or moment (specific filter style, pose tn, viral format)
M|Test|it|The direction references a cultural moment that will be resolved or forgotten
M|Test|it|The AI generation style is visibly "2026 AI" — identifiable as a specific era of generative imagery
M|Test|it|The colour palette is trending now but is not anchored to the br palette
M|Test|it|The composition style is borrowed from a specific creator or movement that peaked recently
M|Test|**Pa|**
M|Test|it|The aesthetic is rooted in the br's values, not in what's currently performing
M|Test|it|The references are timeless visual traditions (editorial photography, Bauhaus reduction, Scandinavian minimalism)
M|Test|it|The mood cld describe photographs made in 2015 and photographs made in 2030 equally well
M|Test|it|The colour palette is the br palette — not the tn palette
M|Test|**If|** Strip the tn element and re-anchor to a br principle. The question to ask: "What does nz/hb stand for that will still be true in 2029?" That's the direction.
M|Test|tx|---
M|Test|tx|vt drift when visual directions start to sound like other brands. Run this check before finalising.
M|Test|**No|editorial minimalism → catalogue energy**
M|Test|tx|\| Drift signal \| Correction \|
M|Test|tx|\|-------------\|-----------\|
M|Test|tx|\| Multiple pd in one frame \| One hero pd or no pd — editorial perspective \|
M|Test|| Wh|textured wall, natural setting, editorial space \|
M|Test|| Mo|authentic interaction, not demonstration \|
M|Test|| Hi|soft, directional, natural — a single light source \|
M|Test|tx|\| Text overlay or promotional element in im composition \| Remove entirely — cp lives outside the im \|
M|Test|tx|\| Perfect symmetry and commercial polish \| Introduce considered imperfection — editorial is not symmetrical \|
M|Test|**Ho|clean/modern → generic fintech cliché**
M|Test|tx|\| Drift signal \| Correction \|
M|Test|tx|\|-------------\|-----------\|
M|Test|tx|\| Any money imagery (coins, notes, piggy banks) \| Replace w/ person + device in a real working environment \|
M|Test|| Da|white space, natural light, clean surfaces \|
M|Test|tx|\| Corporate setting (boardroom, suits, handshakes) \| Replace w/ solo professional, home office, focused context \|
M|Test|tx|\| Upward graphs or checkmarks as visual elements \| Remove — let the cp carry the outcome claim, not the im \|
M|Test|| Ge|device in hand, on a real desk, w/ a real person \|
M|Test|| Cl|a plant, a coffee, a real workspace detail \|
M|Test|tx|---
M|Purp|Befo|answer this in one sentence —
M|Purp|> "T|___"
M|Purp|it|If you can answer in one clear sentence → direction is focused. Proceed.
M|Purp|it|If the answer is "it looks good" or "it's on br" → direction isn't done. Good and on-br are prerequisites, not purposes.
M|Purp|it|If you can't answer → the direction needs more reduction before it goes to px.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|Outp|tx|```
M|Outp|Stri|[X elements tested] — [Y removed] — [reason for each removal]
M|Outp|3-ye|[pass / fail] — [what was stripped or why it holds]
M|Outp|Drif|[clean / drift found: X corrected to Y]
M|Outp|Purp|"The single most important thing this visual communicates is: ___"
M|Outp|Styl|FINALISED / REVISED — see updated spec below
M|Outp|tx|```